Here:
* `\b` - word boundary
* `(?&lt;!&#39;)` - negative lookbehind for `&#39;` as above, that is, match a letter NOT preceded with `&#39;`
* `\p{L}` - the first letter in the word (Unicode)
* `([\p{L}\p{N}]*\b)` - followed by a possibly empty sequence of letters/digits

